  "buggy_functions": ["azx_resume", "azx_rirb_get_response"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "After suspend/resume cycles, if a codec communication timeout occurs during the first resume (while codec initialization is in progress), the error recovery code in azx_rirb_get_response() at line 951 sets chip->single_cmd = 1 to fall back to single command mode. However, the azx_resume() function never resets chip->single_cmd back to its initial value. This causes chip->single_cmd to remain 1 on subsequent suspend/resume cycles. When azx_init_chip() is called during the next resume (line 2561), it checks the condition 'if (!chip->single_cmd)' at line 1222 and skips CORB/RIRB reinitialization because single_cmd is still 1. This prevents proper codec communication setup on resume, leading to timeouts and choppy audio output. The fix requires either: (1) resetting chip->single_cmd = 0 in azx_resume() before calling azx_init_chip(), or (2) ensuring azx_init_chip() properly reinitializes CORB/RIRB even when single_cmd mode was previously activated. Additionally, during codec power management in hda_codec.c, the response_reset flag is improperly cleared when codec->in_pm is true even if there was a communication error, preventing proper error recovery during resume."
}

